[block]
	The Chandy-Lamport-Algorithm is used to retrieve the global state of a distributed system.
[/block]
[block]
	[h2]Conclusion[/h2]
	When a process has received markers from all processes it sends back its recorded state and all recorded messages to the initiating process. [br][br]
	That way a consistent global state inside a certain time-window can be recorded.
[/block]